# API Environment Variables

## Required Variables

### Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://your-mongodb-connection-string

### Authentication
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-minimum-32-characters
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your-refresh-token-secret-key-minimum-32-characters
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRES_IN=7d

### Application
NODE_ENV=development  # Set to "production" in production
PORT=3005

### Storage
STORAGE_DISK=local  # Options: local, s3
# If using S3, also configure:
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-access-key
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret-key
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# AWS_S3_BUCKET=your-bucket-name

### Frontend URL (for CORS)
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

## Production Deployment

When deploying to Vercel/Railway, make sure to set all these environment variables in your deployment platform dashboard.

**Critical for production:**
- `NODE_ENV=production` - Required for secure cookies
- `MONGODB_URI` - Your production MongoDB connection string
- `STORAGE_DISK=s3` - Use cloud storage in production (or configure appropriate storage)
- All JWT secrets should be strong, random strings
